<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-54-0104 </DOCNO><TEXT>In order to study the crystal-phase transition of the monocrystals ofSm(NO/sub 3/)/sub 3/ center dot 6 H/sub 2/O an improved scheme of boththe ac impedance measurements and data processing have been applied.The temperature dependence of the real and the imaginary part of thecomplex dielectric constant {epsilon} along the c-axis in the temperaturerange between room temperature and -55 /sup 0/C in both the cooling andwarming processes are given. Two singularities with a thermal hysteresisare found. The anomalous temperature dependence of {epsilon} between-45 /sup 0/C and 0 /sup 0/C would be related to polymorphic transitionsin the samarium nitrate crystals.</TEXT></DOC>